    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix null pointer dereference in subframe2harqpid for TDD mode 1\n\n### Summary\nThe `subframe2harqpid` function in `eNB_scheduler_primitives.c` was causing null pointer dereferences due to returning invalid HARQ PID values (255) when invalid subframes were provided for TDD mode 1 configuration. This would cause downstream code to access memory incorrectly when using the returned HARQ PID as an array index.\n\nThis fix ensures consistent error handling across all TDD modes by adding proper validation that fails fast with clear error messages.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/LAYER2/MAC/eNB_scheduler_primitives.c`: Modified TDD mode 1 subframe validation to use AssertFatal instead of silent return\n\n### Reproduction\nUnder certain TDD configurations with subframe assignment mode 1, when the scheduler attempted to process subframes other than 2, 3, 7, or 8, the function would return HARQ PID 255. This value was then used as an array index in downstream functions, causing segmentation faults and memory corruption.\n\nThe issue can be observed when running the eNB with TDD configuration and observing crashes during HARQ processing, particularly when invalid subframes are scheduled.\n"
}